This paper deals with the capacity region of a multiple access channel with partial cooperation, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses achievable rate regions and provides numerical results, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) research. Additionally, the paper considers conferencing links and alternative models, which are relevant to communication and networking (cs.CC).
